OL,6,FThey were charged under the Terrorism
OL,7,FAct with carrying or displaying an
OL,8,Farticle to arouse reasonable suspicion
OL,9,Fthat they are supporters of banned
OL,10,Forganisation Hamas, which they denied.
OL,12,FFollowing a two-day trial at
OL,13,FWestminster Magistrates' Court, the
OL,14,Ftrio were found guilty on Tuesday
OL,15,Fafter prosecutors argued it was "no
OL,16,Fcoincidence" the defendants were
OL,17,Fdisplaying the images so soon after
OL,18,Fthe attack.
